
<aside class="bg-dark">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2 text-center">
              <br>
<br>
<br>
                <h2 class="section-heading">Open Data</h2>
                <hr class="light">
                <p class="text-faded">GovMind runs on entirely on public data. The following methods are used to augment our datasets: a) web scraping images, text, and data from public web sites, b) Amazon Turks to structure unorganized data at scale, c) batch snip video into millions of images,  or d) utilizing tabular data from open data sources including Socrata and CKAN. Currently, “open data” largely focuses on tabular data – we have already added image, text, and PDF datasets that are also useful to the community. </p>
                <a href="users/sign_up" class="btn btn-default btn-xl">Learn More</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</aside>

<table class="table table-striped table-bordered table-hover">
  <tr>
    <th class="center">Purpose</th>
    <th class="center">Organization</th>
    <th class="center">Snippet</th>
    <th class="center">Full Dataset</th>
</tr>

  <% @datagalleries.each do |datagallery| %>
<tr>
            <td><%= datagallery.name %></td>
            <td><%= datagallery.organization %></td>
            <td><%= link_to 'Dataset Snippet', datagallery.snippet.url, class:"btn btn-primary"%></td>
            <td><%= link_to 'Full dataset', datagallery.dataset.url, class:"btn btn-primary"%></td>
            <td>
              <div class="btn-group">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary dropdown-toggle" data-toggle="dropdown">
                  Action <span class="caret"></span>
                </button>
              <ul class="dropdown-menu" role="menu">
              <li><%= link_to 'Use', datagallery%></li>
              <li><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_model_path(datagallery), class: "glyphicon glyphicon-pencil" %></li>
             <li><%= link_to 'Destroy', datagallery, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' }, class: "glyphicon glyphicon-trash" %></li>
           </ul>
         </div>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <% end %>
          </table>
<br>

<div class="container">
<%= will_paginate @datagallery, renderer: BootstrapPagination::Rails  %>
</div>

<% if user_signed_in? %>
<% if current_user.admin? %>
<div class="center">
<%= link_to new_datagallery_path, class: "btn btn-primary", data: { no_turbolink: true } do %>
  <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></i> New Dataset
<% end %>
</div>
<% end %>
<% end %>
